## Code Quality (IMPORTANT)

**Code quality specification:** `{{.PromptsDir}}/JAVA_CODE_QUALITY.md`

This project enforces strict code quality standards. You MUST:

1. **Follow the specification** when generating code
2. **Self-review** generated code against the specification
3. **Refactor** any violations immediately
4. **Verify** by running these commands after every change:
   ```bash
   mvn clean compile    # Must succeed â€” zero compilation errors
   mvn test             # Must succeed â€” all tests green
   mvn spotless:check   # Must succeed â€” formatting is correct
   ```

### Quick Quality Checks

| Check | Requirement |
|-------|-------------|
| Method length | Max 30 lines, extract helpers |
| Loops vs Streams | Prefer streams for filter/map/collect |
| Optional | Return types only, use `map`/`orElse`, never `isPresent()+get()` |
| Records | Use for simple data, copy mutable fields |
| Pattern matching | Use `instanceof Type t`, switch expressions |
| Collections | Use `List.of()`, `.toList()`, no `Arrays.asList()` |
| Null handling | `Objects.requireNonNull` in constructors, Bean Validation on DTOs |
| Injection | Constructor injection only, all fields `private final` |
{{- if .HasModule "SQLDatastore"}}
| Pagination | Keyset by ID (`WHERE id > :afterId`), never `OFFSET`/`Pageable` |
| Foreign keys | Never â€” use indexed columns for parent IDs, enforce in service layer |
{{- end}}
{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}
| Batch reads | `findAllByIdIn` / `findAllById` / `multiGet`; chunk IDs at â‰¤1000. Never loop `findById` |
| Bulk writes | `UPDATE`/`DELETE` paired with `LIMIT` in a drain loop. Never unbounded bulk writes |
| Large result drain | Keyset Drain Loop: `findPage(afterId, limit)` until page < limit |
| Denormalization | Snapshot hot fields; materialize aggregates; embed 1-to-few â€” documented with sync path |
{{- end}}

## Code Review Protocol (MANDATORY)

After any code modification, you MUST verify the changes against project standards before completing the turn.

{{- if eq .Agent "claude"}}

**Primary mechanism â€” subagents:**

1. After modifying code, invoke the `code-reviewer` subagent (via the Agent tool with `subagent_type: "code-reviewer"`, or by prompting "use the code-reviewer subagent").
{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}
2. If datastore code (repositories, queries, entities, migrations) changed, also invoke `performance-reviewer`.
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent"}}
{{if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}3{{else}}2{{end}}. If AI-agent code (system prompts, guardrails, tools, agents, knowledge) changed, also invoke `prompt-reviewer`.
{{- end}}

Address findings and re-invoke until reviewers report clean â€” **up to 3 review cycles**. If findings persist after 3 cycles, surface them to the user rather than continuing to iterate.

A Stop hook (`.claude/hooks/require-review.sh`) enforces this by blocking turn completion if the `code-reviewer` subagent was not invoked when Java files changed. The hook is single-shot: once the reviewer has run in a session, subsequent Stops pass silently.

**Manual alternative â€” skills:** run `/review` for general review{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}, `/review-performance` for datastore-focused checks{{- end}}{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent"}}, `/review-prompts` for AI-agent code{{- end}}.

**Security audit (deeper, on-demand):** run `/audit` for the full
security review â€” orchestrator + 5 domain specialists walking the
canonical checklist at `.ai/security-audit/checklist.md` (auth, AI
surface, AIAgent runtime + Java platform, data + events, web + infra
â€” ~173 checks). Produces a severity-sorted findings report at
`.ai/security-audit/findings.md` and a PASS/FAIL verdict. Trigger it
when a security boundary changes (auth, persistence credentials,
broker config, AI tools/guardrails, new controller endpoints) or
before merging a security-relevant PR. The per-turn `code-reviewer`
covers the OWASP basics inline; `/audit` is the deliberate deep
sweep. Full guide: `docs/security-audit.md`.
{{- else if eq .Agent "cursor"}}

Run the `/review` slash command after modifying code{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}, plus `/review-performance` when datastore code changed{{- end}}{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent"}}, plus `/review-prompts` when AI-agent code changed{{- end}}. Address findings and re-run until clean â€” up to 3 cycles.

For a deeper security review, ask Cursor to "run the security audit" â€” the rule at `.cursor/rules/security-audit.mdc` walks the full checklist at `.ai/security-audit/checklist.md` (~173 checks across 5 domains) and writes findings to `.ai/security-audit/findings.md`.

If your Cursor version supports custom agents, `code-reviewer`{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}, `performance-reviewer`{{- end}}{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent"}}, `prompt-reviewer`{{- end}} are defined under `.claude/agents/` â€” the prompts are portable.
{{- else}}

Run the `/review` command after modifying code{{- if or (.HasModule "SQLDatastore") (.HasModule "NoSQLDatastore")}}, plus `/review-performance` when datastore code changed{{- end}}{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent"}}, plus `/review-prompts` when AI-agent code changed{{- end}}. Address findings and re-run until clean â€” up to 3 cycles. The review prompts and patterns live under `.claude/skills/` and `.ai/prompts/`.

For a deeper security review, ask the agent to "run the security audit" â€” it walks the full checklist at `.ai/security-audit/checklist.md` (~173 checks across 5 domains) and writes findings to `.ai/security-audit/findings.md`. Full guide: `docs/security-audit.md`.
