## Boundaries

This project DOES include OAuth2 Resource Server auth scaffolding (Spring Security 6, JWT validation, scope â†’ `SCOPE_*` authority mapping, RFC 7807 problem+json error envelopes). It is dormant by default; set `trabuco.auth.enabled=false` for local dev or `=true` (with `OIDC_ISSUER_URI` + `OIDC_AUDIENCE`) for deployments. The app refuses to boot when that property is unset. See `docs/auth.md` for per-provider recipes and `{{.PromptsDir}}/extend-auth-chain.md` for extending the chain (new tier, new OIDC scope, non-RFC IdP claim extractor, custom filter â€” every flavor demands cross-module updates in lock-step to avoid silent regressions).{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent" }} The AIAgent module additionally ships a legacy API-key path (`app.aiagent.api-key.enabled`, default true) â€” operators populate `agent.auth.keys.*` or use the `local-dev` profile.{{- end }}
{{- if .HasModule "AIAgent" }}

This project DOES include vector-RAG knowledge retrieval (Spring AI 1.0.5 â€” pgvector, Qdrant, or MongoDB Atlas, configurable at `agent.knowledge.vector-store`). `KnowledgeRetriever` is the primary abstraction; `VectorKnowledgeRetriever` wins autowiring when a vector store is selected, `KeywordKnowledgeRetriever` is the fallback. The ambient RAG path (Spring AI's `RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor` on `PrimaryAgent`) uses a separate `TenantFilteringDocumentRetriever` that resolves the tenant filter per call from `CallerContext` â€” both retrievers enforce the same `tenant_id` contract. `DocumentIngestionService` + `IngestionController` (POST `/ingest`, gated by `@RequireScope("partner")`, `@ConditionalOnProperty("agent.ingest.enabled")`, default off) handle document ingestion. Tenant isolation via `CallerIdentity.tenantId()` is enforced at every retriever AND at ingest time â€” caller-supplied `tenant_id` in document metadata is server-side stripped. Do NOT reinvent RAG; extend the existing surface. See `docs/vector-rag.md` for store-specific recipes, `{{.PromptsDir}}/JAVA_CODE_QUALITY.md` Â§6.1.2 for the canonical retriever pattern, `{{.PromptsDir}}/add-knowledge-entry.md` for one-off content additions, `{{.PromptsDir}}/add-retriever.md` for extending the retrieval chain (re-ranking, hybrid, multi-source), and `{{.PromptsDir}}/extend-rag-ingestion.md` for adding new ingestion paths (HTTP endpoints, scheduled jobs, event listeners, custom metadata fields with indexing).

This project DOES include an SSE streaming surface â€” `StreamingController` (`GET /tasks/{taskId}/stream`, `@RequireScope("partner")`) is the canonical reference for the 5-part lifecycle (rate-limit â†’ per-caller cap â†’ BOLA-safe `getTaskForOwner` â†’ named `Consumer<TaskEvent>` listener â†’ paired unsubscribe in all three of `onCompletion` / `onTimeout` / `onError`). Inline `subscribe(id, e -> {...})` lambdas are a regression â€” they cannot be unsubscribed. See `{{.PromptsDir}}/JAVA_CODE_QUALITY.md` Â§6.1.4 for the canonical capture-listener pattern and `{{.PromptsDir}}/add-streaming-endpoint.md` for adding parallel SSE endpoints (per-conversation, per-agent).

This project DOES include a multi-agent orchestration pattern â€” `PrimaryAgent` (user-facing) + `SpecialistAgent` (wrapped in `SpecialistAgentTool` so the primary's LLM can delegate). Adding a new agent variant is always 4 files: a `@Qualifier("xChatModel")` alias bean in `ChatClientConfig`, the agent class as `@Component` (NEVER `@ConditionalOnBean(ChatModel.class)` â€” Spring evaluates that conditional before Spring AI auto-config registers ChatModel, silently failing), the `@Tool` wrapper as `@Component @ConditionalOnBean(<X>Agent.class)` (this conditional IS valid because both classes are user-scanned), and a constructor injection in `PrimaryAgent`. All agents share `@CircuitBreaker(name = "llm")` for global outage coordination and set `ToolCallingChatOptions.maxTokens(2048)` on the builder to bound cost per turn (F-AIAGENT-12 mitigation; Spring AI 1.0.5 ships no tool-call recursion cap). See `{{.PromptsDir}}/add-agent-variant.md` for the procedure and the worked `PlaceholderAgent` example.
{{- end }}

This project does NOT include: identity-provider features (login forms, password handling, MFA enrollment, user management UI, token issuance), frontend/UI, GraphQL, gRPC, WebSockets, Kubernetes manifests, or production database schemas. Placeholder entities should be replaced with real domain objects. For guidance on adding missing capabilities, see `{{.PromptsDir}}/extending-the-project.md`.

